00:23:46,775 --> 00:23:49,437
It's okay.
You can stop now.

228
00:23:50,245 --> 00:23:51,576
Do something.
Somebody!

229
00:23:53,281 --> 00:23:54,942
If I do...

230
00:23:56,451 --> 00:24:01,787
...and you tell anybody,
I'll never hang with you guys again.

231
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:25,903
I never knew Beav could sing.

232
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:35,786
- Beaver, that's beautiful.
- I mean it. Not one word.

233
00:24:35,957 --> 00:24:37,720
Eaver!

234
00:24:37,959 --> 00:24:40,018
You've got a fan.

235
00:24:40,662 --> 00:24:41,720
This yours?

236
00:24:56,444 --> 00:24:59,572
Douglas Cavell.
That's your name, right?

237
00:25:01,449 --> 00:25:02,882
I Duddits.

238
00:25:03,051 --> 00:25:06,077
- What?
- I Duddits!

239
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:08,688
- Duddits?
- Duddits.

240
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:11,081
Duddits, we got to get you home.

241
00:25:22,671 --> 00:25:25,834
Hey, guys! Come here!
Leave the kid there.

242
00:25:26,508 --> 00:25:29,944
Stand right here, Duddits.
Right here with Scooby, okay?

243
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:52,232
Jesus Christ bananas!

244
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:55,062
No way is that
Tina Jean Schlossinger.

245
00:25:55,237 --> 00:25:58,172
Maybe her grandmother.
Good going, Beav.

246
00:25:58,340 --> 00:26:01,537
Holy God. We came all the way
here just for that?

247
00:26:02,277 --> 00:26:06,213
No.
We came for him.

248
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,908
Hey, Pete.
You forgot the dogs.

249
00:26:37,312 --> 00:26:43,774
Weather moving in. Double storm.
Alberta Clipper first, maybe eight inches...

250
00:26:44,119 --> 00:26:46,212
...with a nor'easter on its tail.

251
00:26:47,389 --> 00:26:51,792
- Get on back to the cabin, Henry.
- Heading straight there, Mr. G.

252
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:53,857
- Don't mess around.
- No, sir.

253
00:28:42,737 --> 00:28:44,204
Easy, fella.

254
00:28:44,372 --> 00:28:47,739
Easy. You're okay.
You're all right.

255
00:28:48,243 --> 00:28:50,541
Thank God. Thank God.

256
00:28:50,712 --> 00:28:54,307
Gee, thank God!

257
00:28:54,482 --> 00:28:57,974
I'm lost. I've been lost
in the woods since yesterday.

258
00:28:58,153 --> 00:29:01,714
Let's get you inside.
Get you warm.

259
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:06,024
- How would that be?
- Sure.

260
00:29:20,241 --> 00:29:22,175
Here, let me get that.

261
00:29:26,448 --> 00:29:31,715
- Rick McCarthy.
- Gary Jones. But it's Jonesy to everybody.

262
00:29:31,886 --> 00:29:36,550
Our damn cell phones are on the blink now,
so I can't call for help...

263
00:29:36,724 --> 00:29:38,521
...but our car will be back soon.

264
00:29:38,693 --> 00:29:43,255
I didn't think I'd make it.
I lost the folks I was with.

265
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:47,066
You saved me, that's for sure.

266
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:50,032
What's that?

267
00:29:51,473 --> 00:29:53,373
It's a dreamcatcher.

268
00:29:55,677 --> 00:29:58,874
Indian charm.
Catches nightmares...

269
00:29:59,447 --> 00:30:02,382
...keeps them away.
Keeps you safe down here.

270
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:04,541
I've had enough nightmares.

271
00:30:09,591 --> 00:30:11,320
Been doing that all night.

272
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:14,451
I ate some berries in the dark.

273
00:30:16,798 --> 00:30:19,460
I think they must have upset me.

274
00:30:43,458 --> 00:30:45,050
I know what you're thinking.

275
00:30:45,226 --> 00:30:49,526
Anyone who drinks at 11 a.m. Needs
to take the cure, but I only do it here.

276
00:30:50,031 --> 00:30:52,693
In the real world, I never
drink till after 5:00...

277
00:30:52,867 --> 00:30:55,665
...and if it ever does,
I'm on the wagon for life.

278
00:30:56,304 --> 00:30:57,430
Glad to hear it.

279
00:31:01,009 --> 00:31:02,499
What's the matter with you?

280
00:31:04,178 --> 00:31:07,670
About six months ago,
the day Jonesy got hit...

281
00:31:07,849 --> 00:31:13,583
...I did something terrible with a patient.
Humiliated him. Drove him out of the office.

282
00:31:13,755 --> 00:31:15,746
Barry Neiman.

283
00:31:16,224 --> 00:31:20,354
Couple days ago, I saw his picture
in the paper. He ate himself to death.

284
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:25,455
Mind if I don't use that story
next time I'm trying to sell a Mustang?

285
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:30,767
Henry, you were a lead balloon long before
this porker munched his way to eternity.

286
00:31:30,939 --> 00:31:35,467
Thanks. You're a real comfort.
You got a real delicate touch to you.

287
00:31:38,413 --> 00:31:42,406
Here you go, Rick, buddy.
That will fix you up.

288
00:31:48,856 --> 00:31:53,156
Jesus Christ bananas!
Some fuckarow this is turning into!

289
00:31:55,830 --> 00:31:58,628
- Thanks a lot, Pete.
- Yeah, I think I got it all.

290
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:00,631
What happened to you?

291
00:32:03,605 --> 00:32:08,008
Hi. Joe Clarendon.
Call me Beaver.

292
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:10,269
Rick here had a bad night
in the woods.

293
00:32:10,445 --> 00:32:12,003
Welcome.

294
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:15,581
- Is that frostbite?
- No, I get the same thing from peanuts.

295
00:32:15,750 --> 00:32:16,842
It's allergy.

296
00:32:19,654 --> 00:32:21,383
Grilled cheese, anyone?

297
00:32:21,556 --> 00:32:26,186
- No, the soup's fine for me, thanks.
- I'll bite. Sail it over here.

298
00:32:27,695 --> 00:32:32,029
My mother used to feed me
pea soup when I was feeling...

299
00:32:35,436 --> 00:32:37,336
Bitch in a buzz saw!

300
00:32:37,505 --> 00:32:41,134
I've heard some mighty burps in my time,
but that's the blue ribbon.

301
00:32:41,309 --> 00:32:42,571
I am so embarrassed.

302
00:32:42,744 --> 00:32:44,712
Rick ate some berries in the woods.

303
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:51,279
Oh, my God!

304
00:32:52,654 --> 00:32:54,121
Oh, my God, that's awful!

305
00:32:54,722 --> 00:32:55,814
I'm so sorry!

306
00:32:55,990 --> 00:32:59,926
Rick, buddy, don't worry about it.
There's more room out than in, anyway.

307
00:33:00,094 --> 00:33:02,961
What have you been eating,
woodchuck turds?

308
00:33:05,867 --> 00:33:07,198
Know what I think?

309
00:33:07,902 --> 00:33:11,394
I think you need to lie down
and take you a little nap.

310
00:33:12,306 --> 00:33:14,297
You know, I bet you're right.

311
00:33:14,842 --> 00:33:16,400
I'm just tired, that's all.

312
00:33:17,011 --> 00:33:19,741
- Come on.
- My hat.

313
00:33:21,149 --> 00:33:22,480
Beaver?

314
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:27,178
In here.

315
00:33:31,559 --> 00:33:34,392
Thank you for taking me in.
Thank you both.

316
00:33:34,562 --> 00:33:38,430
- Shit, anybody would have.
- Maybe. Maybe not.

317
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:41,330
All right, this is in case
you have to urk...

318
00:33:41,502 --> 00:33:45,165
...if you can't get to the bathroom,
which is the third door to your left.

319
00:33:45,339 --> 00:33:48,399
If you go in the first,
you'll take a shit in the closet.

320
00:33:48,910 --> 00:33:50,935
If you need anything, we're outside.

321
00:34:05,993 --> 00:34:07,551
Fuck me, give me some air!

322
00:34:07,729 --> 00:34:10,926
We got any gas masks handy?
We need a biohazard team in here.

323
00:34:12,433 --> 00:34:16,369
- Wanna hear what will freak you out more?
- Not really.

324
00:34:16,838 --> 00:34:18,362
You know his huge stomach?

325
00:34:18,539 --> 00:34:22,873
When he got here, his stomach was normal,
but his chest was out to here!

326
00:34:23,044 --> 00:34:24,511
I wish Henry was here.

327
00:34:24,679 --> 00:34:26,374
He's a shrink, not an internist.

328
00:34:26,581 --> 00:34:29,709
He went to med school.
Did you?

329
00:34:31,252 --> 00:34:33,083
I thought about it.

330
00:34:47,435 --> 00:34:49,232
You better get a run at it.

331
00:34:59,247 --> 00:35:00,976
- Shit!
- Watch it!

332
00:35:01,149 --> 00:35:02,343
What the hell?

333
00:35:29,911 --> 00:35:35,349
- Pete, are you okay?
- No, I broke my leg! Man, my damn leg!

334
00:35:35,516 --> 00:35:38,485
Okay. Hang on. Hang on a second.

335
00:35:38,653 --> 00:35:40,883
- I'm caught! I can't...
- God!

336
00:35:48,262 --> 00:35:53,393
- God.
- Henry! A little help here!

337
00:35:53,901 --> 00:35:55,960
Hang on, Pete. Hang on.

338
00:35:56,137 --> 00:35:59,971
- Okay. Here comes the seat belt.
- I just opened that beer.

339
00:36:02,143 --> 00:36:03,770
I got you.

340
00:36:15,923 --> 00:36:17,618
How's your leg?

341
00:36:18,693 --> 00:36:23,392
Well, it ain't broken.
It's just locked up, is all.

342
00:36:43,317 --> 00:36:45,877
You don't suppose
he got exposed to radiation?

343
00:36:46,053 --> 00:36:50,353
I saw that once in a movie.
Guy ended up bald as Telly what's-his-fuck.

344
00:36:50,524 --> 00:36:54,984
This guy's got plenty of hair. But that
red mark got bigger while I was watching it.

345
00:36:58,966 --> 00:37:02,493
- What are you doing?
- Peanut butter calms me down.

346
00:37:03,170 --> 00:37:07,129
- Somebody else might want to use that jar.
- I'll leave some.

347
00:37:09,176 --> 00:37:10,666
Beav.

348
00:37:12,079 --> 00:37:13,603
Beaver.

349
00:37:18,486 --> 00:37:20,681
Criminettlies!

350
00:37:37,438 --> 00:37:39,338
I think it's a woman.

351
00:37:40,775 --> 00:37:43,676
I ought to warn you.
I'm gonna strangle this broad.

352
00:37:43,844 --> 00:37:46,745
- I'd guess she's already dead.
- I'll strangle her anyway.

353
00:37:46,914 --> 00:37:48,973
She almost got us both killed.

354
00:37:50,284 --> 00:37:53,776
Hello! Here we come, ma'am.
Don't be startled.

355
00:38:03,331 --> 00:38:04,889
Hello?

356
00:38:05,766 --> 00:38:09,566
Forget it, H. She's gone.

357
00:38:12,573 --> 00:38:14,200
Hello!

358
00:38:16,010 --> 00:38:22,415
Ma'am, can you hear me?
Are you okay? Can you hear me?

359
00:38:25,353 --> 00:38:29,016
I wonder if maybe that's how
they say hello around here.

360
00:38:29,190 --> 00:38:33,024
Listen, Miss Road Kill,
you almost got us dead.

361
00:38:34,128 --> 00:38:36,062
Say something.

362
00:38:37,064 --> 00:38:40,056
I have to find Rick.

363
00:38:42,970 --> 00:38:45,700
- Okay.
- Rick.

364
00:38:50,311 --> 00:38:51,938
Yeah.

365
00:38:53,381 --> 00:38:55,781
Fuck me, Freddy.

366
00:39:02,189 --> 00:39:06,125
- What's all that red stuff on their fur?
- Just like McCarthy's cheek.

367
00:39:06,727 --> 00:39:10,754
- I never saw anything like this before.
- Even the bears look scared.

368
00:39:10,931 --> 00:39:14,423
- Of what? Where are they going?
- It's not where that worries me...

369
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:17,093
...it's what are they running away from?

370
00:39:25,546 --> 00:39:26,911
What the hell?

371
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:32,510
This could be perfect.
They can get Stinky to a hospital.

372
00:39:32,686 --> 00:39:33,914
Hey, you guys!

373
00:39:38,159 --> 00:39:43,620
- We need some help! Got a sick guy inside!
- <i>This area is under temporary quarantine.</i>

374
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:46,198
- <i>Stay where you are.</i>
- What quarantine?

375
00:39:46,367 --> 00:39:50,770
- We got a sick guy down here!
- We need your help here!

376
00:39:50,938 --> 00:39:53,839
- We got a real sick guy here!
- Take him with you now!

377
00:39:54,408 --> 00:39:59,539
<i>Glad you're okay. This situation</i>
<i>will be resolved in 24 to 48 hours.</i>

378
00:40:02,049 --> 00:40:03,744
Kiss my bender!

379
00:40:28,776 --> 00:40:32,337
I gotta ask you, old buddy.
Because I'm confused.

380
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:36,847
- Is this SSDD or not?
- Definitely not.

381
00:40:37,017 --> 00:40:38,678
Different shit today, Pete.

382
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:42,482
And a pretty weird day so far,
if you want to know.

383
00:40:42,656 --> 00:40:44,419
Over here.

384
00:40:49,096 --> 00:40:50,563
There you go.

385
00:40:51,665 --> 00:40:53,257
Easy.

386
00:40:58,239 --> 00:41:03,506
It's nine miles to Hole in the Wall.
I think I can manage it.

387
00:41:04,478 --> 00:41:07,003
I'll bring the snowmobile back
and get you both.

388
00:41:07,181 --> 00:41:11,174
Now, Pete, you listen to me.
Don't go back to the car for beer.

389
00:41:11,352 --> 00:41:16,756
- Stay with her. Keep her warm.
- Right hand to God, Dr. D.

390
00:41:17,491 --> 00:41:18,753
Henry!

391
00:41:18,926 --> 00:41:21,190
If we die before you get back...

392
00:41:21,929 --> 00:41:25,228
...promise you'll tell everybody
she wasn't my date.

393
00:41:34,175 --> 00:41:37,269
I'm telling you, Jonesy,
I don't like this at all.

394
00:41:37,444 --> 00:41:41,744
This is turning into a double fuckarow.
A real jobba-nobba.

395
00:42:49,617 --> 00:42:52,711
- Rick, you okay?
- I'm a little sick, fellas.

396
00:42:52,886 --> 00:42:57,016
- I just need to make a little room.
- McCarthy, Rick, open up, man.

397
00:42:57,191 --> 00:42:59,955
- Go away!
- Open the door or we break it down.

398
00:43:00,127 --> 00:43:03,756
- Can't a man have some privacy?
- Rick, where are you bleeding from?

399
00:43:03,931 --> 00:43:07,389
Bleeding? I'm not bleeding.

400
00:43:10,638 --> 00:43:14,039
- Let's do it.
- I'm not positive I wanna go in there.

401
00:43:14,208 --> 00:43:18,304
What if he's dying? Scooby-Dooby-Doo,
we got some work to do now.

402
00:43:18,679 --> 00:43:21,239
On three. Ready?

403
00:43:21,548 --> 00:43:24,984
One... Two...

404
00:43:25,619 --> 00:43:28,486
Hold it!
What if we just bounce off?

405
00:43:30,157 --> 00:43:34,093
- No bounce, no play.
- Right. No bounce, no play.

406
00:43:34,795 --> 00:43:36,456
One...

407
00:43:36,930 --> 00:43:40,331
And a two... Three!

408
00:43:47,941 --> 00:43:51,001
Oh, fuck! Oh, man!
Fuck!

409
00:43:51,278 --> 00:43:53,746
I don't want to see this!
I can't see this.

410
00:43:53,914 --> 00:43:57,475
- Shut up a minute. Mr. McCarthy? Rick?
- Is he still alive?

411
00:43:57,651 --> 00:44:00,779
I don't know. Rick?
Rick, are you...?

412
00:44:01,422 --> 00:44:05,119
Oh, man! Jonesy, if he can still do that,
he must be alive.

413
00:44:05,292 --> 00:44:07,385
Can you hear me?
I think he's dead.

414
00:44:07,561 --> 00:44:09,859
Bullshit! He dropped a clinker!
I heard it.

415
00:44:10,030 --> 00:44:13,591
- I don't think that was a clinker.
- That's enough, snap out of it!

416
00:44:14,435 --> 00:44:16,801
- Oh, my God!
- My God!

417
00:44:20,874 --> 00:44:22,808
- No!
- No?

418
00:44:25,512 --> 00:44:30,006
Good move! It's trapped.
Got nowhere to go but the septic tank.

419
00:44:55,309 --> 00:44:57,072
Oh, shit!

420
00:44:57,644 --> 00:45:01,080
- Listen, Beaver, we're gonna change places.
- What?

421
00:45:01,248 --> 00:45:03,614
- One of us is gonna go to the shed.
- No way!

422
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:06,480
Shut up and listen!
There's friction tape there.

423
00:45:06,653 --> 00:45:09,349
You go get it, come back.
We'll tape the lid down.

424
00:45:09,556 --> 00:45:11,717
Then we're gonna get the hell out of here!

425
00:45:12,559 --> 00:45:15,357
- You get the tape, Jonesy.
- Don't be brave, Beav.

426
00:45:15,529 --> 00:45:17,895
You're faster than me.
I'll sit on Thumper.

427
00:45:18,065 --> 00:45:21,193
No, if it does get out, you can't fight it.
Not with your hip.

428
00:45:21,702 --> 00:45:24,569
Oh, my God!
Goddamn it! Go!

429
00:45:35,883 --> 00:45:37,714
- And Beav?
- Yeah?

430
00:45:37,951 --> 00:45:39,919
Sit tight, buddy.

431
00:45:44,625 --> 00:45:46,149
Okay.

432
00:46:38,879 --> 00:46:41,370
All right. Okay.

433
00:46:48,856 --> 00:46:53,725
Shit! Earth to Jonesy!
Come in, Jonesy!

434
00:47:05,772 --> 00:47:09,367
Jonesy. Jonesy.

435
00:47:11,979 --> 00:47:15,039
Calm down now. Okay.

436
00:47:16,517 --> 00:47:17,814
Okay.

437
00:47:18,418 --> 00:47:22,081
Okay, here it is. Okay.

438
00:47:27,327 --> 00:47:29,557
Find the damn tape!

439
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:44,395
Where is it?

440
00:48:48,475 --> 00:48:49,601
Coming, Beav!

441
00:49:06,293 --> 00:49:08,523
Beaver! Beav!

442
00:49:08,862 --> 00:49:11,330
I got the... What the...

443
00:49:18,171 --> 00:49:19,570
Jonesy, get out of here!

444
00:49:20,540 --> 00:49:21,632
Beaver.

445
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:24,776
- Get out! Shut the door!
- No.

446
00:49:26,513 --> 00:49:27,844
Run, Jonesy.

447
00:50:27,040 --> 00:50:29,065
You killed him.

448
00:50:29,209 --> 00:50:31,700
You killed Beaver.

449
00:50:31,878 --> 00:50:34,403
You killed him, you fuck!

450
00:52:05,138 --> 00:52:07,698
What do you want?

451
00:53:32,859 --> 00:53:36,556
The men call the red stuff Ripley,
after the broad in the <i>Alien</i> movies.

452
00:53:36,730 --> 00:53:39,290
We eradicate the animals
as they flee the Blue Zone.

453
00:53:39,432 --> 00:53:40,558
And the populace?

454
00:53:40,700 --> 00:53:44,898
We're bringing civilians to Gosselin's.
We'll detain them till we figure this out.

455
00:53:45,071 --> 00:53:50,532
And Owen? This time the ETs belong
to you. That's right, bucko.

456
00:53:50,710 --> 00:53:52,803
- You'll be Blue Boy leader.
- Finally.

457
00:53:52,979 --> 00:53:55,504
- How many left?
- About a hundred.

458
00:53:55,682 --> 00:53:59,049
Yeah. Not nearly enough
for a serious incursion.

459
00:53:59,219 --> 00:54:01,483
My guess is,
it's a crash-landing.

460
00:54:01,655 --> 00:54:05,250
They've never picked terrain like this before.
Or cold weather.

461
00:54:05,425 --> 00:54:06,756
What's your call?

462
00:54:06,927 --> 00:54:10,021
The biggest threat
is them getting out of our net.

463
00:54:10,196 --> 00:54:11,993
Crash-landing or not...

464
00:54:12,165 --> 00:54:14,963
...they'll try to get out
and spread the infection.

465
00:54:16,303 --> 00:54:20,740
