01:23:14,837 --> 01:23:17,305
This gives you an idea
what we're up against.

690
01:23:19,308 --> 01:23:22,368
If anybody's thinking,
"Those poor, helpless little folk...

691
01:23:22,545 --> 01:23:26,641
...all naked and unarmed beside
their crashed intergalactic Winnebago...

692
01:23:26,816 --> 01:23:29,808
...what kind of a dog,
what kind of a monster...

693
01:23:29,986 --> 01:23:32,750
...could hear that heartbreak
and go in just the same?"

694
01:23:32,922 --> 01:23:38,019
- Well, I'm that dog. I'm that monster.
- <i>We are helpless. We are dying.</i>

695
01:23:38,194 --> 01:23:41,027
These mothers are as harmless
as a fox in a henhouse.

696
01:23:41,197 --> 01:23:44,064
And I'm here to kick some ass!
Are you with me?

697
01:23:44,233 --> 01:23:46,030
- Yes, boss!
- Roger that, boss.

698
01:23:46,269 --> 01:23:47,429
Right on, boss.

699
01:23:48,504 --> 01:23:50,597
<i>Don't hurt us.</i>

700
01:23:55,011 --> 01:23:56,808
I have a visual.

701
01:23:59,849 --> 01:24:01,612
<i>Holy shit!</i>

702
01:24:01,784 --> 01:24:03,718
<i>Damn, look at the size of that.</i>

703
01:24:05,188 --> 01:24:09,784
<i>Blue Boy group, this is Blue Boy leader.</i>
<i>Target imminent. Move to level 4 readiness.</i>

704
01:24:09,959 --> 01:24:12,120
Gentlemen, lock and load.

705
01:24:14,063 --> 01:24:15,394
Hellfires are hot.

706
01:24:17,099 --> 01:24:18,361
Sing it out, Owen!

707
01:24:18,868 --> 01:24:24,431
Blue Boy group, this is Blue Boy leader.
Clean up the forest and get rid of this trash!

708
01:24:24,607 --> 01:24:27,201
- Don't hurt us.
- Please, don't hurt us.

709
01:24:27,376 --> 01:24:30,436
- There is no infection here.
- We are helpless.

710
01:24:30,746 --> 01:24:33,214
- Fire at will!
- Fire!

711
01:25:46,489 --> 01:25:48,480
<i>Owen, get them out of there!</i>

712
01:25:49,692 --> 01:25:50,989
<i>It's gonna blow!</i>

713
01:25:51,494 --> 01:25:55,157
Blue Boy group, withdraw at once.
I repeat, cease firing and back off!

714
01:25:55,331 --> 01:25:57,697
- We can get them!
- <i>It's self-destructing. Back off!</i>

715
01:25:58,100 --> 01:26:00,933
- Blue Boy group, get out of there!
- We're on top of it!

716
01:26:01,837 --> 01:26:03,737
<i>Owen, pull out now!</i>

717
01:26:03,906 --> 01:26:07,239
- <i>Pull out! Get out of there!</i>
- Pull out!

718
01:26:34,003 --> 01:26:39,066
Jonesy, I've been thinking about our friend.
Our Scooby-Doo buddy.

719
01:26:39,675 --> 01:26:43,406
For a long time I thought he was sent to us
to warn us about something.

720
01:26:43,679 --> 01:26:46,648
- I could never figure what it was.
- Don't talk about him.

721
01:26:46,816 --> 01:26:51,048
Not till today.
It was this, right now.

722
01:26:51,787 --> 01:26:57,089
- He wanted to warn us.
- Go ahead, Pete. Tell me about your friend.

723
01:26:57,259 --> 01:27:02,219
- Did he show you that nifty trick?
- No. Jonesy's right.

724
01:27:02,665 --> 01:27:06,761
- Come on, Pete. Let's talk.
- Bite my bag, motherfucker!

725
01:27:10,639 --> 01:27:15,906
All right, Pete, I'll bite.
Your bag and everything else.

726
01:27:19,849 --> 01:27:23,012
No, no! You bastard! No!

727
01:27:31,961 --> 01:27:33,895
Pete.

728
01:28:22,878 --> 01:28:25,210
Don't talk to him!
Get out of there!

729
01:28:29,585 --> 01:28:32,179
- What's up?
- Thank God you came by, governor.

730
01:28:32,488 --> 01:28:35,082
I'm broke down here and fearing for my life.

731
01:28:35,758 --> 01:28:37,385
That's a good-looking dog.

732
01:28:37,560 --> 01:28:39,619
- Where you headed?
- Gosselin's.

733
01:28:39,795 --> 01:28:42,389
Any chance you're going near there?

734
01:28:42,865 --> 01:28:44,594
That's where I'm going.

735
01:28:45,501 --> 01:28:49,198
Well, I believe your tailgate has come open.

736
01:28:55,678 --> 01:28:57,407
Let's take a look.

737
01:29:05,087 --> 01:29:08,181
I see you have some cargo
you're taking to Blue Base.

738
01:29:32,081 --> 01:29:34,447
Got a treat for you, lke.

739
01:29:37,386 --> 01:29:42,016
All you can eat.
Eat all the red stuff.

740
01:29:43,692 --> 01:29:49,426
Good doggy. Yes.
Good boy.

741
01:29:50,032 --> 01:29:54,298
Have your fill.
Tasty, tasty.

742
01:29:54,470 --> 01:29:56,529
Eat all you want...

743
01:29:59,508 --> 01:30:04,138
Jonesy.
What are you up to?

744
01:30:39,448 --> 01:30:40,847
<i>Jonesy!</i>

745
01:31:01,870 --> 01:31:03,599
Oh, God!

746
01:31:55,958 --> 01:32:00,054
Halt or we'll fire!
You cannot leave the quarantine zone!

747
01:32:00,229 --> 01:32:02,356
- Halt!
- I think I just about halted here.

748
01:32:08,003 --> 01:32:09,527
Come with me, Owen.

749
01:32:09,705 --> 01:32:12,731
I'll show you things
you'll wish you'd never seen.

750
01:32:27,956 --> 01:32:30,686
- How long we gotta be here?
- It'll be all right.

751
01:32:35,264 --> 01:32:38,859
- I demand to see my lawyer!
- There must be something they can do.

752
01:32:41,170 --> 01:32:42,933
Don't worry, you'll be fine.

753
01:32:43,138 --> 01:32:45,231
- When do we get out?
- Within hours.

754
01:32:45,407 --> 01:32:49,639
- You can't do this to people in America!
- I told you to stay over there!

755
01:32:49,812 --> 01:32:52,280
- My wife...
- Government's doing everything they can...

756
01:32:52,448 --> 01:32:55,474
...to get you out of here.
Please don't worry. It's all right.

757
01:32:55,651 --> 01:32:58,211
We're doing everything
to make sure you're safe.

758
01:32:58,387 --> 01:33:01,254
We'll get you back to your homes
within hours.

759
01:33:10,866 --> 01:33:12,527
All clear.

760
01:33:35,057 --> 01:33:37,821
Can I help you, sir?
What's your name?

761
01:33:37,993 --> 01:33:42,020
- Henry. Dr. Henry Devlin.
- A doctor? Good.

762
01:33:42,197 --> 01:33:43,858
We need doctors in there.

763
01:33:45,734 --> 01:33:48,259
Come on, laddie, I'll buy you a cup.

764
01:33:50,272 --> 01:33:54,902
- You, sir, where you from?
- Boston.

765
01:33:55,577 --> 01:34:01,140
Beantown? Great city.
We'll have you back there in no time.

766
01:34:01,316 --> 01:34:03,147
Maybe by morning.

767
01:34:04,253 --> 01:34:06,187
Hurry up, bucko.

768
01:34:16,632 --> 01:34:19,328
You see that crud on the faces
of children...

769
01:34:19,501 --> 01:34:23,665
...you know why I relish a turn
in the country like we had today.

770
01:34:24,640 --> 01:34:29,168
You were excellent out there, O.
It made me feel very proud to...

771
01:34:32,114 --> 01:34:35,948
Abe?
Abe, you okay?

772
01:34:37,352 --> 01:34:39,343
Abe?

773
01:34:46,228 --> 01:34:51,564
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine.
I must be getting too old for this shit.

774
01:34:52,701 --> 01:34:55,499
I don't know what the hell that was about.

775
01:35:09,451 --> 01:35:11,783
It's the only way, Owen.

776
01:35:12,588 --> 01:35:15,250
We've got to cauterize the site.

777
01:35:16,859 --> 01:35:18,850
They've all got to die.

778
01:35:20,262 --> 01:35:21,854
It's the only way.

779
01:35:22,097 --> 01:35:23,894
But we don't know that.

780
01:35:24,099 --> 01:35:28,536
The studies point to the strong possibility
of recovery for many exposed subjects.

781
01:35:28,704 --> 01:35:31,434
The studies show squat,
that's what they show.

782
01:35:31,607 --> 01:35:34,838
If Matheson had been in my spot
for the last quarter-century...

783
01:35:34,977 --> 01:35:37,605
...you'd have never made
it to your first jerk-off.

784
01:35:38,046 --> 01:35:42,415
Those gray bastards would have had you
for lunch back in Armpit, Kentucky.

785
01:35:42,584 --> 01:35:45,917
Some get better. At least
half will be over it in a few days...

786
01:35:46,088 --> 01:35:48,283
Which ones, Mother Teresa?

787
01:35:48,457 --> 01:35:52,723
Can you guarantee they won't take it home
like a present for the family?

788
01:35:52,928 --> 01:35:56,830
I'll tell you what you should be worried
about. What should be on your mind.

789
01:35:56,999 --> 01:35:58,626
Not these few unfortunates.

790
01:35:59,101 --> 01:36:01,661
What you should be worried
about is a hitchhiker.

791
01:36:01,837 --> 01:36:03,304
- What?
- A hitchhiker.

792
01:36:03,472 --> 01:36:06,566
Our greatest fear is that a grayboy
would catch a ride...

793
01:36:06,742 --> 01:36:10,735
...with somebody and would carry them
out of here, without being consumed.

794
01:36:11,013 --> 01:36:14,039
To scatter the infection,
like Johnny-fucking-Appleseed.

795
01:36:14,216 --> 01:36:16,480
- Are you sure there isn't such a person?
- No.

796
01:36:16,652 --> 01:36:19,212
But I am sure that if there is one
he won't get out.

797
01:36:19,388 --> 01:36:22,084
Not with the net my boys
put up around the Blue Zone.

798
01:36:22,357 --> 01:36:25,155
And if we do a thorough job
on the ones we've got.

799
01:36:25,327 --> 01:36:29,730
If we don't get gooey about the little picture
when our job is taking care of the big one.

800
01:36:30,399 --> 01:36:31,730
<i>Capisce?</i>

801
01:36:32,134 --> 01:36:36,093
Owen, if you think this is easy for me,
you're crazier than my mother was.

802
01:36:37,673 --> 01:36:39,265
Those poor schmucks.

803
01:36:40,075 --> 01:36:43,841
They drive Chevrolets, shop at Wal-Mart...

804
01:36:44,012 --> 01:36:46,003
...never miss an episode of <i>Friends</i>.

805
01:36:47,082 --> 01:36:48,947
These are Americans.

806
01:36:50,686 --> 01:36:52,881
The idea of slaughtering Americans...

807
01:36:55,691 --> 01:36:57,921
...it just turns my stomach.

808
01:37:01,964 --> 01:37:06,196
But I'll do it.
I'll do it because it needs to be done.

809
01:37:07,669 --> 01:37:12,129
So if we start at 2, we can be done
by 2:30. And it's all behind us.

810
01:37:13,075 --> 01:37:15,066
Except for the dreams.

811
01:37:18,046 --> 01:37:20,446
Yeah, except for them.

812
01:37:32,694 --> 01:37:36,095
What are you gonna tell Rita
about what you did here?

813
01:37:36,398 --> 01:37:39,959
What are you gonna tell Katrina
when she's old enough to ask?

814
01:37:43,638 --> 01:37:48,234
You know me, don't you? I don't remember
when we met, but you know me.

815
01:37:48,477 --> 01:37:52,379
We don't have time to screw around.
You've got two problems.

816
01:37:52,547 --> 01:37:55,846
- One you know about, one you don't.
- Go ahead.

817
01:37:56,451 --> 01:38:02,287
Your mentor, Colonel Curtis, he's gone
insane from hunting aliens for 25 years.

818
01:38:02,457 --> 01:38:06,450
Now he wants you to help him
kill hundreds of innocent people.

819
01:38:07,529 --> 01:38:09,520
- Who are you?
- Me?

820
01:38:09,698 --> 01:38:12,690
Talk about that later,
once we get out of here.

821
01:38:13,668 --> 01:38:16,694
You're predictable.
You won't let me burn on this fence...

822
01:38:16,872 --> 01:38:19,534
...any more than you'll help
Curtis kill those people.

823
01:38:19,708 --> 01:38:23,474
What you're thinking now is whether
that digital sat-scan transmitter...

824
01:38:23,645 --> 01:38:26,705
...in your duffle bag will
let you get through to somebody.

825
01:38:27,749 --> 01:38:30,718
Somebody named General Matheson.

826
01:38:34,022 --> 01:38:39,426
"Sometimes we have to kill,
but our real job is to save lives."

827
01:38:43,598 --> 01:38:45,896
Your father was a great soldier.

828
01:38:46,368 --> 01:38:47,835
Those were his last words.

829
01:38:48,003 --> 01:38:50,164
You carry his picture with you always.

830
01:38:53,308 --> 01:38:54,935
Tell me everything.

831
01:38:56,111 --> 01:38:58,045
You'll save these people.

832
01:38:58,213 --> 01:39:01,671
When we're done talking, get on the
transmitter, contact Matheson.

833
01:39:01,850 --> 01:39:03,112
Cavalry rides in.

834
01:39:03,285 --> 01:39:06,584
That takes care of problem number one.
Now comes the hard part.

835
01:39:06,755 --> 01:39:11,317
You think the infection's been contained,
that there's no hitchhiker.

836
01:39:11,493 --> 01:39:15,190
You're wrong. He's riding with
my best friend on Earth.

837
01:39:15,363 --> 01:39:18,264
A guy named Gary Jones.
And he's out there.

838
01:39:18,834 --> 01:39:23,168
You and I don't get after him right away,
he'll get out of my range...

839
01:39:23,371 --> 01:39:26,306
...and some kind of shit
is gonna hit the planetary fan.

840
01:39:40,689 --> 01:39:42,816
Our nightmare hitchhiker.

841
01:39:43,425 --> 01:39:48,954
And all Dr. Mystery wants is a free pass
so he can catch his friend.

842
01:39:49,131 --> 01:39:52,396
- Very convenient.
- I'm saying you ought to hear his story.

843
01:39:52,801 --> 01:39:54,234
Okay. Where is he?

844
01:39:54,402 --> 01:39:56,199
Had him taken to the tractor shed.

845
01:39:56,671 --> 01:40:00,072
Okay. I'll check him out
and we can compare notes.

846
01:40:00,242 --> 01:40:01,937
Whatever you say, boss.

847
01:40:08,817 --> 01:40:12,218
Come on, come on. Time's a-wasting.

848
01:40:22,164 --> 01:40:24,291
All right, lad, open up.

849
01:40:42,717 --> 01:40:44,014
Dr. Boston?

850
01:40:45,420 --> 01:40:46,751
Are you in here?

851
01:40:48,156 --> 01:40:49,623
I'm here.

852
01:40:49,758 --> 01:40:51,055
Where I've been put.

853
01:40:52,227 --> 01:40:54,457
A prisoner on my own damn property.

854
01:40:59,234 --> 01:41:00,565
Let's go!

855
01:41:02,270 --> 01:41:03,669
Come on, let's go.

856
01:41:10,312 --> 01:41:11,870
Get in!

857
01:41:13,982 --> 01:41:15,711
You almost ran me down.

858
01:41:15,884 --> 01:41:18,785
Figured you'd read my mind
and get out of the way.

859
01:41:21,890 --> 01:41:26,725
<i>Blue Unit, stand down.</i>
<i>You are under regular Army command.</i>

860
01:41:26,895 --> 01:41:28,886
<i>Put down your weapons at once.</i>

861
01:41:29,965 --> 01:41:32,490
<i>Your mission is rescinded.</i>

862
01:41:32,667 --> 01:41:36,000
<i>This is no longer a Blue Unit operation.</i>

863
01:41:36,171 --> 01:41:41,302
<i>Put down your arms.</i>
<i>Repeat, put down your arms.</i>

864
01:41:41,476 --> 01:41:44,707
<i>General Matheson has assumed command.</i>

865
01:41:54,089 --> 01:41:55,351
Okay, Owen.

866
01:41:56,024 --> 01:41:57,321
Okay.

867
01:41:58,026 --> 01:42:01,154
You just drove over the Curtis line.

868
01:42:03,331 --> 01:42:05,196
- Where we going?
- South.

869
01:42:05,367 --> 01:42:08,131
All I know right now.
Just get me in range of Jonesy...

870
01:42:08,303 --> 01:42:10,203
...we'll know everything we need to know.

871
01:42:33,928 --> 01:42:36,726
That's some gun.
Can I have a look?

872
01:42:44,005 --> 01:42:47,338
- Kind of flashy for a guy like you, isn't it?
- It's a gift.

873
01:42:47,509 --> 01:42:49,170
I know.

874
01:42:51,346 --> 01:42:52,836
Where are you, Jonesy?

875
01:42:53,014 --> 01:42:56,074
Pick up the phone. Call 1-800-HENRY.

876
01:43:12,600 --> 01:43:14,534
Hello? Jonesy!

877
01:43:14,703 --> 01:43:18,400
Jesus Christ, I knew it was you.
Where's he taking you?

878
01:43:19,174 --> 01:43:21,369
Massachusetts? He is?

879
01:43:21,676 --> 01:43:25,203
Duddits? Okay, I will.
You hang in there, Jonesy.

880
01:43:25,380 --> 01:43:26,677
Jonesy?

881
01:43:27,349 --> 01:43:28,748
He hung up.

882
01:43:29,851 --> 01:43:31,512
Give me back my gun.

883
01:43:33,788 --> 01:43:36,222
- We gotta go to Derry.
- That where they're going?

884
01:43:36,391 --> 01:43:39,519
No, they're going towards Massachusetts.
We need Duddits.

885
01:43:39,694 --> 01:43:42,720
Jonesy says Mr. Gray is afraid of Duddits.

886
01:43:42,897 --> 01:43:46,958
Your buddy, he's still alive
after all this time with Mr. Gray?

887
01:43:47,135 --> 01:43:49,968
Yeah, he's immune.
I think it's because he died.

888
01:43:51,706 --> 01:43:55,870
He got hit by a car
and his heart stopped. Twice.

889
01:43:56,044 --> 01:43:57,875
I don't think he even knows it.

890
01:43:58,213 --> 01:44:01,740
He came back from the dead.
Must have changed him somehow.

891
01:44:03,485 --> 01:44:08,013
It's almost like Duddits saw
this whole thing coming. Is that it?

892
01:44:10,392 --> 01:44:14,328
Jonesy told me it was Duddits
who drew him into the accident.

893
01:44:14,496 --> 01:44:17,124
If we catch him,
we're gonna have to kill him.

894
01:44:17,499 --> 01:44:21,060
You know we have to do it.
It's the only way to stop Mr. Gray...

895
01:44:21,636 --> 01:44:23,661
...assuming we can catch him.

896
01:44:26,808 --> 01:44:29,174
When was the last time you saw Duddits?

897
01:44:29,344 --> 01:44:30,971
Long time ago.

898
01:44:32,080 --> 01:44:33,479
Years.

899
01:44:34,916 --> 01:44:37,180
What makes you so sure he can help?

900
01:44:37,752 --> 01:44:39,379
Duddits can do anything.

901
01:44:40,355 --> 01:44:44,621
I didn't understand that then,
but I think it's always been true.

902
01:44:45,360 --> 01:44:47,851
He's the one who made us like this.

903
01:44:48,029 --> 01:44:50,827
- Like what?
- You know, weird.

904
01:45:07,081 --> 01:45:08,673
He's been waiting for you.

905
01:45:08,850 --> 01:45:10,215
Blizzard slowed us up.

906
01:45:10,385 --> 01:45:12,546
Henny, Henny.

907
01:45:13,688 --> 01:45:15,155
Henny.

908
01:45:19,928 --> 01:45:22,123
I miss you, Henny.

909
01:45:22,297 --> 01:45:24,265
I miss you.

910
01:45:26,868 --> 01:45:28,426
Henny.

911
01:45:28,670 --> 01:45:31,002
Long time, Henny.

912
01:45:36,211 --> 01:45:40,341
- My God, Roberta, what is it?
- Lymphocytic leukemia.

913
01:45:43,418 --> 01:45:47,878
I'm gonna let you take him,
but I have to tell you why.

914
01:45:48,923 --> 01:45:51,551
Just now, when he was getting ready...

915
01:45:53,428 --> 01:45:56,829
...Henry he was so excited.

916
01:45:56,998 --> 01:45:59,899
Like he hasn't been in such a long time.

917
01:46:06,941 --> 01:46:08,704
I think...

918
01:46:08,877 --> 01:46:12,438
...that if he's with you,
he might die happy...

919
01:46:12,914 --> 01:46:15,246
...instead of in this awful room.

920
01:46:17,719 --> 01:46:21,211
Be sure the parka stays on tight.
Cold devastates him.

921
01:46:22,223 --> 01:46:25,386
The medication and instructions are in here.

922
